description: A Wisconsin judge ruled Monday that two Republican-backed measures may appear on the April ballot, granting the party a win over left-wing activists who sued to block them.

title: Lawyers for Islamic State NYC Terrorist Decry Testimony of Victims' Families
description: Lawyers for Sayfullo Saipov, who killed eight people on a Lower Manhattan bike path, argue that the prosecution is unfairly using victim-impact testimony to push for the death penalty.

title: Kamala Harris blasted for posting photo of herself with masked child: 'The rage I feel'
description: Vice President Kamala Harris faced backlash for tweeting an image of her standing with a masked child to promote Black female leadership on Sunday.

title: John Malkovich discusses disappearance of 'close' friend Julian Sands: 'It's a very sad event'
description: Actors John Malkovich and Julian Sands met on "The Killing Fields" in the '80s and remained very "close" through the years, even living together at one point.

title: Turkey hit by another 6.4 magnitude earthquake, leaving at least three dead
description: Turkey was hit by a 6.4 magnitude earthquake on Monday, just two weeks after a 7.8 magnitude quake toppled thousands of buildings and killed about 45,000 people.

title: Prophetic South Park clip from 2005 goes viral for mocking transgender ideology: ‘Brutally honest take’
description: A South Park clip from 2005 surged across Twitter after commentators observed how it predicted and slammed aspects of modern transgender ideology.
